    <section class="section">
        <h2>7. Cookies and Analytics</h2>
        
        <h3>What Are Cookies?</h3>
        <p>Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit our website. They help us understand how you use our site and improve your browsing experience.</p>
        
        <h3>Types of Cookies We Use</h3>
        
        <h4>Essential Cookies</h4>
        <p>These cookies are necessary for the website to function properly. They include:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Cookie Consent:</strong> Remembers your cookie preferences so we don't ask you repeatedly</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h4>Analytics Cookies (Optional - Requires Consent)</h4>
        <p>With your consent, we use Google Analytics to understand how visitors interact with our website. This helps us improve our content and services. Google Analytics collects information such as:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Pages you visit on our website</li>
            <li>Time spent on each page</li>
            <li>How you arrived at our site (e.g., search engine, direct link)</li>
            <li>Your approximate location (city/region level only)</li>
            <li>Device type and browser information</li>
            <li>Anonymized IP address (we have IP anonymization enabled for GDPR compliance)</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p><strong>Important:</strong> Google Analytics cookies are only loaded after you explicitly accept cookies through our consent banner. We do not track your activity unless you provide consent.</p>
        
        <h3>Managing Your Cookie Preferences</h3>
        <p>When you first visit our website, you'll see a cookie consent banner asking for your permission to use analytics cookies. You can:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Accept:</strong> Allow Google Analytics to help us improve the website</li>
            <li><strong>Decline:</strong> Use the website without analytics tracking</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>To change your cookie preferences after making a choice, you can clear your browser's local storage for this website, which will reset your consent and show the banner again on your next visit.</p>
        
        <h3>Google Analytics Privacy</h3>
        <p>Google Analytics processes data on behalf of Hixa Heating. We have configured Google Analytics with:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>IP anonymization enabled (your IP address is anonymized)</li>
            <li>Data sharing with Google disabled</li>
            <li>Advertising features disabled (no remarketing or personalized ads)</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>For more information about how Google processes data, visit <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.</p>
        
        <h3>Browser Cookie Controls</h3>
        <p>You can also control cookies through your browser settings:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Block all cookies (may affect website functionality)</li>
            <li>Delete existing cookies</li>
            <li>Set preferences for specific websites</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>For instructions on managing cookies in your browser, visit your browser's help section.</p>
    </section>

